{"word":"στίλβω","slug":"στίλβω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>στίλβω</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>chiefly in <a href='S:present tense'>pres.</a> and <a href='S:imperfect tense'>imperf.</a>\n<p/><i>to glisten</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>; <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> cogn., <el>στ. ἀστραπάς</el> <i>to flash</i> lightning, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>:—<a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a> <i>to shine, be bright</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/>"}]}